description = Use when building or debugging the runtime that actually executes an agent loop — how it dispatches tools, retries, checkpoints, sandboxes, or stays within budget — or when looking up or saving a runtime concept; not when choosing the control-flow pattern the loop follows (that is agent-architectures), nor managing what occupies the context window (that is context-engineering). Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled agent-runtime knowledge on demand — the execution layer (harness) that runs an agent: the loop driver, tool dispatch, retries and idempotency, durable execution and restart-survival, session and state persistence, sandboxing, runaway-guards and budgets, triggers and scheduling, and sub-agent spawning.
